4.17 1.12 1.11 2.7 1.62 4.24 1.79v4.03c-1.44-.05-2.89-.35-4.2-.97-.57-.26-1.1-.59-1.62-.93-.01 2.92.01 5.84-.02 8.75-.08 1.4-.54 2.79-1.35 3.94-1.31 1.92-3.58 3.17-5.91 3.21-1.43.08-2.86-.31-4.08-1.03-2.02-1.19-3.44-3.37-3.65-5.71-.02-.5-.03-1-.01-1.49.18-1.9 1.12-3.72 2.58-4.96 1.66-1.44 3.98-2.13 6.15-1.72.02 1.48-.04 2.96-.04 4.44-.99-.32-2.15-.23-3.02.37-.63.41-1.11 1.04-1.36 1.75-.21.51-.15 1.07-.14 1.61.24 1.64 1.82 3.02 3.5 2.87 1.12-.01 2.19-.66 2.77-1.61.19-.33.4-.67.41-1.06.1-1.79.06-3.57.07-5.36.01-4.03-.01-8.05.02-12.07z" fill="#000000"/></svg>`},
    { key:['YOUTUBE','YT'], platform:'YOUTUBE', id:'yt', label:'Subscribers', icon:`<svg class="platform-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path fill="#FF0000" d="M23.5 6.2a3 3 0 0 0-2.1-2.1C19.5 3.5 12 3.5 12 3.5s-7.5 0-9.4.6a3 3 0 0 0-2.1 2.1C0 8.1 0 12 0 12s0 3.9.5 5.8a3 3 0 0 0 2.1 2.1c1.9.6 9.4.6 9.4.6s7.5 0 9.4-.6a3 3 0 0 0 2.1-2.1C24 15.9 24 12 24 12s0-3.9-.5-5.8zM9.5 15.5v-7l6 3.5-6 3.5z"/></svg>`}
  ];

  const cards = PLATS.map(p => {
    // find platform value in byPlat by matching keys
    let val = null;
    for (const k of Object.keys(byPlat||{})){
      if (p.key.some(kk => k.includes(kk))) { val = byPlat[k]; break; }
    }
    if (val==null || val==='') return '';
    let series = null;
    for (const k of Object.keys(growthSeries||{})){
      if (p.key.some(kk => k.includes(kk))) { series = growthSeries[k]; break; }
    }
    const growthOptions = getRosterGrowthOptions(series || []);
    const defaultPeriod = '30';
    const initial = growthOptions[defaultPeriod] || null;
    let growthClass = 'empty';
    let growthArrow = '';
    let growthValue = '‚Äî';
    let growthTooltip = '';
    if (initial && Number.isFinite(initial.pct)) {
      const isUp = initial.pct >= 0;
      growthClass = isUp ? 'up' : 'down';
      growthArrow = isUp ? '‚Üë' : '‚Üì';
      const sign = initial.pct > 0 ? '+' : '';
      growthValue = `${sign}${formatGrowthPercent(initial.pct)}%`;
      growthTooltip = buildGrowthTooltipText(initial.pct, initial.refLabel);
    }
    let growthDataAttrs = '';
    [30, 90, 365].forEach(days => {
      const opt = growthOptions[days];
      if (!opt || !Number.isFinite(opt.pct)) return;
      growthDataAttrs += ` data-growth-${days}="${opt.pct.toFixed(4)}" data-growth-ref-${days}="${escAttr(opt.refLabel)}"`;
    });
    const tooltipAttr = growthTooltip ? ` data-tooltip="${escAttr(growthTooltip)}"` : '';
    const growthHtml = `
      <div class="roster-growth-wrap">
        <div class="roster-growth ${growthClass}" data-growth-period="${defaultPeriod}" data-growth-talent="${escAttr(talentName)}" data-growth-platform="${escAttr(p.platform)}"${growthDataAttrs}${tooltipAttr}>
          <span class="roster-growth-arrow">${growthArrow}</span>
          <span class="roster-growth-value">${growthValue}</span>
        </div>
        <div class="roster-growth-menu">
          <button type="button" data-growth-select="30">Ultimi 30 giorni</button>
          <button type="button" data-growth-select="90">Ultimi 90 giorni</button>
          <button type="button" data-growth-select="365">Ultimi 12 mesi</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    `;
    const link = getRosterSocialLink(talentName, p.platform);
    const cardAttrs = link
      ? ` class="roster-card ${p.id} roster-card-link" href="${escAttr(link)}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"`
      : ` class="roster-card ${p.id}"`;
    const cardTag = link ? 'a' : 'div';
    const cardHtml = `<${cardTag}${cardAttrs}><div class="top">${p.icon}<div class="value">${formatFollowersCompactByPlatform(val, p.platform)}</div></div><div class="label">${p.label}</div></${cardTag}>`;
    return `<div class="roster-card-wrap">${cardHtml}${growthHtml}</div>`;
  }).filter(Boolean).join('');

  const chartData = buildRosterChartCards(rows, talentName);
  const chartClass = chartData.count === 3
    ? 'three-cols'
    : (chartData.count === 2 ? 'two-cols' : 'one-col');
  const charts = chartData.count
    ? `<div class="roster-chart-inline ${chartClass}">${chartData.cardsHtml}</div>`
    : '';
  const backBtn = `
    <button class="roster-back-btn" type="button" data-roster-back aria-label="Torna al roster">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M15 18l-6-6 6-6"/></svg>
    </button>`;
  const avatar = `
    <div class="roster-detail-avatar" aria-hidden="true">
      <img src="${escAttr(rosterPhotoSrc(talentName))}" alt="" loading="eager">
    </div>`;
  const content = cards ? `<div class="roster-grid">${cards}</div>` : `<div class="roster-empty">Nessuna piattaforma disponibile per questo talent.</div>`;
  const html = `
    ${avatar}
    <div class="roster-detail">
      ${backBtn}
      <div class="roster-detail-content">
        ${content}
        ${charts}
      </div>
    </div>`;
  rosterEl.innerHTML = html;
  rosterEl.style.display = 'block';
}

/* Event Delegation for Bucket Dropdowns */
if (els.kpis) {
    els.kpis.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
        // Toggle Dropdown
        const titleWrapper = e.target.closest('.bucket-title-wrapper.has-dropdown');
        if (titleWrapper) {
            e.stopPropagation();
            const bucket = titleWrapper.dataset.bucket;
            const dropdown = document.getElementById(`dropdown-${bucket}`);
            
            // Close all others
            document.querySelectorAll('.bucket-dropdown').forEach(d => {
                if(d !== dropdown) d.classList.remove('show');
            });
            
            if (dropdown) dropdown.classList.toggle('show');
            return;
        }

        // Handle Option Click
        const optBtn = e.target.closest('.bucket-opt');
        if (optBtn) {
            e.stopPropagation();
            const dropdown = optBtn.closest('.bucket-dropdown');
            const bucketId = dropdown.id.replace('dropdown-', '');
            const val = optBtn.dataset.val; // ALL, ADV, NO_ADV
            
            // Update State
            bucketFilters[bucketId] = val;
            
            // Rerender to apply filters
            renderResults();
            return;
        }
    });
}

// Close bucket dropdowns on outside click
document.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
    if (!e.target.closest('.bucket-title-wrapper') && !e.target.closest('.bucket-dropdown')) {
        document.querySelectorAll('.bucket-dropdown').forEach(d => d.classList.remove('show'));
    }
});


/* --- MODALE PREVIEW LOGIC --- */
function openPreview(url) {
  if (!url) return;

  // FIX GOOGLE DRIVE: usa /preview per l'iframe
  let embedUrl = url;

  // Esempi che vogliamo sistemare:
  // https://drive.google.com/file/d/ID/view?usp=sharing
  // -> https://drive.google.com/file/d/ID/preview
  if (url.includes('drive.google.com') && url.includes('/view')) {
    // togliamo eventuali query ?usp=...
    const [base] = url.split('?');
    embedUrl = base.replace('/view', '/preview');
  }

  // L'iframe usa la versione /preview (niente richiesta accesso)
  els.previewIframe.src = embedUrl;
  els.previewModal.style.display = 'flex';

  // Il bottone "Apri esterno" apre invece il link originale
  els.btnOpenExternal.onclick = () => window.open(url, '_blank');
}

function closePreview() {
  els.previewModal.style.display = 'none';
  els.previewIframe.src = ""; // Stop video/audio
}

// Bind Close Events (lasciali invariati)
if (els.btnClosePreview) els.btnClosePreview.onclick = closePreview;
if (els.previewModal) {
  els.previewModal.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
     if(e.target === els.previewModal) closePreview();
  });
}


/* Eventi click tabella - MODIFICATO PER APRIRE MODALE */
document.addEventListener('click', e=>{
  const tr = e.target.closest('tr[data-link]');
  if (tr) {
    const url = tr.getAttribute('data-link');
    if (url) {
      openPreview(url);
      // NON usiamo window.open qui, usiamo la modale
    }
  }
});

/* Toggle KPI Mode */
if (els.kpis) {
  els.kpis.addEventListener('click', e=>{
    if (e.target.closest('.pill')) {
      if (searchMode === 'estimate') return;
      aggMode = (aggMode === 'media' ? 'somma' : 'media');
      renderResults();
    }
  });
}
if (els.btnReset) {
  els.btnReset.onclick = resetAllSelections;
}


/* NEW EXPORT LOGIC WITH DROPDOWN */

/* 1. Toggle Dropdown EXPORT (CSV) */
if (els.btnExportMenu) {
  els.btnExportMenu.onclick = (e) => {
    e.stopPropagation();
    const isVisible = els.exportDropdown.style.display === 'flex';
    els.exportDropdown.style.display = isVisible ? 'none' : 'flex';
  };
}

/* Toggle dropdown modalit√† PDF nel popup */
if (els.pdfModeMenuToggle && els.pdfModeDropdown) {
  els.pdfModeMenuToggle.onclick = (e) => {
    e.stopPropagation();
    const isVisible = els.pdfModeDropdown.style.display === 'flex';
    els.pdfModeDropdown.style.display = isVisible ? 'none' : 'flex';
    
    // Toggle active state styling
    if (!isVisible) els.pdfModeMenuToggle.classList.add('open');
    else els.pdfModeMenuToggle.classList.remove('open');
  };

  // Click sulle voci Media / Somma / Media + Somma
  els.pdfModeDropdown.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
    const btn = e.target.closest('[data-mode]');
    if (!btn) return;
    exportAggMode = btn.getAttribute('data-mode'); // "media" | "somma" | "both"
    updatePdfModeLabel();
    els.pdfModeDropdown.style.display = 'none';
    els.pdfModeMenuToggle.classList.remove('open');
  });
}

/* 2. Close dropdowns if clicked outside */
document.addEventListener('click', () => {
  if (els.exportDropdown) els.exportDropdown.style.display = 'none';
  if (els.pdfModeDropdown) {
      els.pdfModeDropdown.style.display = 'none';
      if (els.pdfModeMenuToggle) els.pdfModeMenuToggle.classList.remove('open');
  }
});


/* 3. CSV Export Function */
function exportCSV() {
    // Use filtered rows logic (respects bucket filters too)
    const rows = rowsFiltered().filter(r => {
        // Apply bucket filters to CSV export rows too!
        const b = getBucket(r[COLS.type]);
        const filter = bucketFilters[b] || 'ALL';
        if (filter === 'ALL') return true;
        if (filter === 'ADV') return r.isAdv;
        if (filter === 'NO_ADV') return !r.isAdv;
        return true;
    });

    if (rows.length === 0) return;

    /* --- SUMMARY CALCULATION --- */
    const periodLabel = computePeriodLabel(rows);
const ts = computeContentTypesSummary(rows);
const contentSummary = ts.text;
const totalPubs = ts.totalPublications || 0;


    const summaryRows = [
        `"Periodo dell'attivit√†";"${periodLabel}"`,
        `"Contenuti pubblicati";"${contentSummary}"`,
        `"Pubblicazioni totali";"${totalPubs}"`,
        "" // Empty line separator
    ];
    
    // Headers
    const headers = [
        "Attivit√†", "Mese", "Contenuto", "Impression", "Reach",
        "Click Link", "Click Tag", "Mi Piace", "Commenti", "Salvataggi", "Condivisioni", "Link"
    ];
    
    // Rows
    const csvRows = rows.map(r => [
        `"${String(r[COLS.brand]||'').replace(/"/g, '""')}"`,
        `"${String(monthName(r[COLS.month])).replace(/"/g, '""')}"`,
        `"${String(r[COLS.type]||'').replace(/"/g, '""')}"`,
        toNum(r[COLS.views]),
        toNum(r[COLS.reach]),
        toNum(r[COLS.linkClicks]),
        toNum(r[COLS.tagClicks]),
        toNum(r[COLS.likes]),
        toNum(r[COLS.comments]),
        toNum(r[COLS.saves]),
        toNum(r[COLS.shares]),
        `"${String(r[COLS.link]||'').replace(/"/g, '""')}"`
    ].join(';')); // Using semicolon for Excel Euro compatibility often better, or use comma
    
    // Combine with BOM for Excel UTF-8
    const csvContent = "\uFEFF" + summaryRows.join('\n') + "\n" + headers.join(';') + "\n" + csvRows.join('\n');
    
    const blob = new Blob([csvContent], { type: 'text/csv;charset=utf-8;' });
    const url = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
    
    const link = document.createElement("a");
    link.href = url;
    const brandPart = selectedBrandFullLabel() || 'Brand';

    const filename = `Report_${sel.talent || 'Talent'}_${brandPart}.csv`;

    link.setAttribute("download", filename);
    document.body.appendChild(link);
    link.click();
    document.body.removeChild(link);
}

/* 4. Bind CSV Button */
if (els.btnExportCsv) {
  els.btnExportCsv.onclick = exportCSV;
}


/* MODALE PDF */
const modal = document.getElementById('pdfCommentModal');
const btnPdfConfirm = document.getElementById('btnPdfConfirm');
const btnPdfSkip = document.getElementById('btnPdfSkip');
const pdfInput = document.getElementById('pdfCommentInput');
const btnClosePdfModal = document.getElementById('btnClosePdfModal'); // X Button

function closePdfModal() {
  modal.style.display = "none";
}

/* Open Modal (Attached to Main PDF Button) */
if (els.btnExportPdf) {
  els.btnExportPdf.onclick = () => {
    pdfInput.value = "";
    btnPdfConfirm.disabled = true; // start disabled

    // Di default usiamo la modalit√† attuale della webapp (Media / Somma)
    exportAggMode = "both"; 
    updatePdfModeLabel();

    modal.style.display = "flex";
    pdfInput.focus();
  };
}


// Close modal on outside click (Overlay) or X button
if(els.pdfCommentModal) {
    els.pdfCommentModal.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
        // If the click is on the overlay itself (not the inner content), close it
        if (e.target === els.pdfCommentModal) {
            closePdfModal();
        }
    });
}
if(btnClosePdfModal) {
  btnClosePdfModal.onclick = closePdfModal;
}

/* Keyboard Event for ESC */
document.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
  if (e.key === "Escape" && els.pdfCommentModal.style.display === "flex") {
    closePdfModal();
  }
});


/* Input Listener for Validation */
pdfInput.addEventListener("input", (e) => {
    // Enable only if trimmed text is not empty
    btnPdfConfirm.disabled = e.target.value.trim().length === 0;
});

/* Actions */
btnPdfConfirm.onclick = () => {
  modal.style.display = "none";
  handleExport(pdfInput.value.trim(), exportAggMode);
};

btnPdfSkip.onclick = () => {
  modal.style.display = "none";
  handleExport(null, exportAggMode);
};



/* EXPORT PDF - IMPLEMENTAZIONE CON BASE64 */

function addDisclaimer(doc) {
  const disclaimer = PDF_DISCLAIMER;
  doc.setFont("helvetica", "bold");
  doc.setFontSize(11);
  doc.setTextColor(170, 170, 170);

  const charSpace = 2.5; 
  const textOptions = { charSpace };
  const baseWidth = doc.getTextWidth(disclaimer);
  const extraWidth = disclaimer.length * charSpace;
  const trueWidth = baseWidth + extraWidth;
  const x = (1920 - trueWidth) / 2;
  const y = 1080 - 28;

  doc.text(disclaimer, x, y, textOptions);
}

async function handleExport(userComment, mode){
  const startTime = Date.now();

  // Check validation
  if (!sel.brand && !sel.talent) return; 
  
  // NOTE: rowsFiltered() returns data filtered by global params.
  // We need to apply the specific bucket filters for the PDF too to respect WYSIWYG
  let rows = rowsFiltered();
  
  // Filter Rows by active Bucket Filters to ensure PDF matches UI data
  const activeBucketKeys = Object.keys(bucketFilters);
  if (activeBucketKeys.length > 0) {
        rows = rows.filter(r => {
            const b = getBucket(r[COLS.type]);
            const filter = bucketFilters[b] || 'ALL';
            if (filter === 'ALL') return true;
            if (filter === 'ADV') return r.isAdv;
            if (filter === 'NO_ADV') return !r.isAdv;
            return true;
        });
  }

  if (rows.length === 0) return;

  // Show Loading Overlay
  if(els.pdfLoadingOverlay) {
    els.pdfLoadingOverlay.style.display = 'flex';
  }
  
  // Await a tick to ensure UI updates
  await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 100));

  // Modalit√† scelta per l'export (se non passata, usa quella attuale)
  const exportMode = mode || aggMode;
  const prevAggMode = aggMode;

  // Flag per sapere se usare il layout compatto nel PDF
  let useCompactLayout = false;

  // Usiamo la UI come "set cinematografico":
  if (exportMode === "media" || exportMode === "somma") {
    aggMode = exportMode;
    renderResults();

  } else if (exportMode === "both") {
    /* --- SMART LOGIC: MEDIA + SUM --- */
    
    // 1. Calculate Content Counts per Bucket (on filtered rows)
    const counts = {};
    rows.forEach(r => {
        const b = getBucket(r[COLS.type]);
        counts[b] = (counts[b] || 0) + 1;
    });

    // 2. Render Media to capture cards
    aggMode = "media";
    renderResults();
    const mediaCards = Array.from(els.kpis.querySelectorAll('.summary-card'));
    const mediaMap = new Map();
    mediaCards.forEach(card => {
      const m = card.className.match(/bucket-([A-Z]+)/);
      if (m) mediaMap.set(m[1], card.cloneNode(true));
    });

    // 3. Render Sum to capture cards
    aggMode = "somma";
    renderResults();
    const sumCards = Array.from(els.kpis.querySelectorAll('.summary-card'));
    const sumMap = new Map();
    sumCards.forEach(card => {
      const m = card.className.match(/bucket-([A-Z]+)/);
      if (m) sumMap.set(m[1], card.cloneNode(true));
    });

    // 4. Construct Final Display
    els.kpis.innerHTML = "";
    els.kpis.style.display = '';
    els.kpis.classList.add("summary-both");

    let totalBoxCount = 0;
    const processedBuckets = new Set();

    // Iterate using mediaCards order to preserve sorting
    mediaCards.forEach(dummy => {
        const m = dummy.className.match(/bucket-([A-Z]+)/);
        const bucket = m ? m[1] : null;
        if (!bucket || processedBuckets.has(bucket)) return;
        
        const count = counts[bucket] || 0;

        if (count > 1) {
            // MULTIPLE ITEMS: Show Both
            if(mediaMap.has(bucket)) els.kpis.appendChild(mediaMap.get(bucket));
            if(sumMap.has(bucket)) els.kpis.appendChild(sumMap.get(bucket));
            totalBoxCount += 2;
        } else {
            // SINGLE ITEM: Show Hybrid (Single Card)
            // Use Media data to ensure Reach is visible (not N/A)
            if(mediaMap.has(bucket)) {
                const hybrid = mediaMap.get(bucket);
                
                // Hide "Media" Pill
                const pill = hybrid.querySelector('.pill');
                if(pill) pill.style.display = 'none';

                // Change Subtitle to generic "Views"
                const sub = hybrid.querySelector('.sub');
                if(sub) {
                   // Replace "Views medie" or "Views totali" with just "Views"
                   sub.innerText = sub.innerText.replace("Views totali", "Views").replace("Views medie", "Views");
                }
                
                els.kpis.appendChild(hybrid);
                totalBoxCount += 1;
            }
        }
        processedBuckets.add(bucket);
    });

    // Handle any buckets that might only exist in sum (rare edge case but good to cover)
    sumCards.forEach(dummy => {
        const m = dummy.className.match(/bucket-([A-Z]+)/);
        const bucket = m ? m[1] : null;
        if (!bucket || processedBuckets.has(bucket)) return;
        // Same logic: single or multiple?
        const count = counts[bucket] || 0;
        if(count > 1) {
             const sommaCard = sumMap.get(bucket);
             if(sommaCard) { els.kpis.appendChild(sommaCard); totalBoxCount++; }
        } else {
             // Fallback to sum card if media not found, but try media first
             const hybrid = mediaMap.get(bucket) || sumMap.get(bucket);
             const pill = hybrid.querySelector('.pill'); if(pill) pill.style.display='none';
             const sub = hybrid.querySelector('.sub'); if(sub) sub.innerText = sub.innerText.replace("Views totali", "Views").replace("Views medie", "Views");
             els.kpis.appendChild(hybrid);
             totalBoxCount++;
        }
        processedBuckets.add(bucket);
    });

    // 5. Layout Decision based on TOTAL BOXES
    if (totalBoxCount > 4) {
      els.kpis.classList.add("summary-both-compact");
      useCompactLayout = true;
    } else {
      els.kpis.classList.remove("summary-both-compact");
    }
  }

  const { jsPDF } = window.jspdf;
  const doc = new jsPDF({
    orientation: 'landscape',
    unit: 'px',
    format: [1920, 1080]
  });

  // Qui creiamo lo stage
  const stage = document.createElement('div');
  stage.className = 'pdf-stage';

  // Se devo usare il layout compatto, lo applico ORA
  if (exportMode === "both" && useCompactLayout) {
    stage.classList.add("pdf-compact");
  }

  // ADDED: Class to handle margins if comment is present
  if (userComment) {
    stage.classList.add("pdf-has-comment");
  }

  document.body.appendChild(stage);

  try {
    // 1. COVER
    if (PDF_COVER_BASE64) {
       doc.addImage(PDF_COVER_BASE64, "PNG", 0, 0, 1920, 1080);
    } else {
       // Fallback black
       doc.setFillColor(2, 6, 23);
       doc.rect(0, 0, 1920, 1080, "F");
       doc.setFontSize(60);
       doc.setTextColor(255,255,255);
       doc.text("REPORT ANALISI INSIGHT", 960, 540, { align: "center" });
    }

    // 2. DASHBOARD PAGE
    doc.addPage([1920, 1080], "landscape");
    stage.innerHTML = "";
    
    // Build Content
   const wrapper = document.createElement('div');
wrapper.className = 'pdf-wrapper';

const pageContent = document.createElement('div');
pageContent.className = 'page-content';

wrapper.appendChild(pageContent);
stage.appendChild(wrapper);


    // Logo
    const logoImg = document.createElement('img');
    logoImg.src = document.getElementById('agencyLogo').src;
    logoImg.className = 'pdf-logo';
    stage.appendChild(logoImg);

    // Title
    const titleEl = document.createElement('h1');
    titleEl.className = 'pdf-main-title';
    const tLabel = sel.talent ? sel.talent.toUpperCase() : "REPORT";
    const bLabel = (selectedBrandFullLabel() || "").toUpperCase();
    titleEl.innerHTML = `${esc(tLabel)} <span style="color:#6b7280; margin:0 10px;">‚Äî</span> <span class="brand-highlight">${esc(bLabel)}</span>`;
    pageContent.appendChild(titleEl);

    // Comment
    if (userComment) {
      const commentEl = document.createElement('div');
      // REMOVED fixed margin from inline style, handled by CSS .pdf-comment
      commentEl.style.cssText = "font-size:24px; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.7); text-align:center; font-style:italic; white-space:pre-wrap; max-width:900px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;";
      commentEl.classList.add('pdf-comment'); // Added class
      commentEl.innerText = userComment;
      pageContent.appendChild(commentEl);
    }

    // Clone Dashboard elements using DOM CLONING to preserve style
    const miniClone = els.mini.cloneNode(true);
    miniClone.style.display = 'grid'; 
    pageContent.appendChild(miniClone);

    const kpisClone = els.kpis.cloneNode(true);
    kpisClone.style.display = 'flex';
    pageContent.appendChild(kpisClone);

    

    // Screenshot
    const canvas1 = await html2canvas(stage, { scale: 2, useCORS: true, backgroundColor: null });
    doc.addImage(canvas1.toDataURL('image/jpeg', 0.8), 'JPEG', 0, 0, 1920, 1080);
    addDisclaimer(doc);

    // 3. TABLE PAGES
    // Use the filtered rows for the table pages as well
    const tbody = document.createElement('tbody');
    // We need to re-render the rows to HTML TRs because 'rows' is data objects
    // reusing the render logic from renderResults but for the PDF set
    
    // Sort rows for consistency
    const sortedRows = [...rows].sort((a,b) => (monthKey(a[COLS.month]) - monthKey(b[COLS.month])) || norm(a[COLS.brand]).localeCompare(norm(b[COLS.brand])) || norm(a[COLS.type]).localeCompare(norm(b[COLS.type]), undefined, {numeric:true}));
    
    const trs = sortedRows.map(r => {
        const tr = document.createElement('tr');
        if(r[COLS.link]) tr.setAttribute('data-link', r[COLS.link]);
        tr.innerHTML = `<td>${esc(formatBrandForTable(r[COLS.brand]))}</td><td>${esc(monthName(r[COLS.month]))}</td><td>${esc(r[COLS.type])}</td><td>${disp(r[COLS.views])}</td><td>${disp(r[COLS.reach])}</td><td>${disp(r[COLS.linkClicks])}</td><td>${disp(r[COLS.tagClicks])}</td><td>${disp(r[COLS.likes])}</td><td>${disp(r[COLS.comments])}</td><td>${disp(r[COLS.saves])}</td><td>${disp(r[COLS.shares])}</td>`;
        return tr;
    });

    const ROWS_PER_PAGE = 10;
    const theadClone = document.querySelector('#table thead').cloneNode(true);

    for (let i = 0; i < trs.length; i += ROWS_PER_PAGE) {
       doc.addPage([1920, 1080], "landscape");
       stage.innerHTML = "";
       
       // Logo (re-add)
       const pageLogo = logoImg.cloneNode(true);
       stage.appendChild(pageLogo);

       const tableContent = document.createElement('div');
       tableContent.className = 'page-content';
       
       const table = document.createElement('table');
       table.appendChild(theadClone.cloneNode(true));
       const tbodyChunk = document.createElement('tbody');
       const chunk = trs.slice(i, i + ROWS_PER_PAGE);
       chunk.forEach(r => tbodyChunk.appendChild(r.cloneNode(true))); // Need to append to body
       table.appendChild(tbodyChunk);
       tableContent.appendChild(table);
       stage.appendChild(tableContent);

       const canvasT = await html2canvas(stage, { scale: 2, useCORS: true, backgroundColor: null });
       doc.addImage(canvasT.toDataURL('image/jpeg', 0.8), 'JPEG', 0, 0, 1920, 1080);
       addDisclaimer(doc);

       // Restore Link Overlay Logic
       const stageRect = stage.getBoundingClientRect();
       const trNodes = Array.from(tbodyChunk.querySelectorAll('tr'));
       for (const tr of trNodes) {
           const linkUrl = tr.getAttribute('data-link');
           if (linkUrl) {
               const rect = tr.getBoundingClientRect();
               doc.link(
                   rect.left - stageRect.left, 
                   rect.top - stageRect.top, 
                   rect.width, 
                   rect.height, 
                   { url: linkUrl }
               );
           }
       }
    }

    // 4. BACK COVER
    if (PDF_BACK_BASE64) {
        doc.addPage([1920, 1080], "landscape");
        doc.addImage(PDF_BACK_BASE64, "PNG", 0, 0, 1920, 1080);
    } else {
        doc.addPage([1920, 1080], "landscape");
        doc.setFillColor(2, 6, 23);
        doc.rect(0, 0, 1920, 1080, "F");
        doc.setFontSize(40);
        doc.setTextColor(255,255,255);
        doc.text("GRAZIE", 960, 540, { align: "center" });
    }

    // --- WAIT FOR MINIMUM TIME *BEFORE* SAVING ---
    const elapsed = Date.now() - startTime;
    if (elapsed < 2000) {
        await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 2000 - elapsed));
    }

    const brandSlugRaw = selectedBrandFullLabel() || 'General';
    const brandSlug = sel.brand === "__ALL__" ? "Tutte-le-attivita" : String(brandSlugRaw).replace(/\s+/g, '-');
    const talentSlug = String(sel.talent||'Report').replace(/\s+/g, '-');
    doc.save(`Report_${talentSlug}_${brandSlug}.pdf`);

  } catch(e) {
    console.error(e);
    alert("Errore PDF: " + e.message);
  } finally {
    document.body.removeChild(stage);
    
    if(els.pdfLoadingOverlay) els.pdfLoadingOverlay.style.display = 'none';

    // Ripristina stato originale della UI
    aggMode = prevAggMode;
    els.kpis.classList.remove("summary-both");
    els.kpis.classList.remove("summary-both-compact");
    renderResults();
  }
}



/* ====== NLP LOGIC (Smart Search Bar) ====== */

function detectTalentCandidates(normQuery){
  const clean = normQuery.replace(/[.,;:!?]/g,' '); 
  const words = clean.split(/\s+/).filter(Boolean); 
  const wordSet = new Set(words);
  
  // Exact match on full name
  const exact = TALENT_VOCAB.filter(t => normQuery.includes(t.norm)).map(t => t.name);
  if (exact.length) return exact;
  
  // Token match (e.g. "Nicky" matches "Nicky Passarella")
  return TALENT_VOCAB.filter(t => t.tokens.some(tok => wordSet.has(tok))).map(t => t.name);
}

function detectRosterTalentCandidates(normQuery){
  const list = (Array.isArray(ROSTER_TALENTS) && ROSTER_TALENTS.length) ? ROSTER_TALENTS : ROSTER_ORDER;
  const clean = normQuery.replace(/[.,;:!?]/g,' ');
  const words = clean.split(/\s+/).filter(Boolean);
  const wordSet = new Set(words);
  const exact = list.filter(name => normQuery.includes(norm(name)));
  if (exact.length) return exact;
  return list.filter(name => {
    const tokens = norm(name).split(/\s+/).filter(w => w.length > 2 && !TALENT_STOPWORDS.has(w));
    return tokens.some(tok => wordSet.has(tok));
  });
}

function detectBrand(normQuery){
  if (!BRAND_VOCAB.length) return null; 
  const q = norm(normQuery); 
  let best = null; 
  let bestLen = 0;
  for (const b of BRAND_VOCAB){ 
      if (q.includes(b.norm) && b.norm.length > bestLen){ 
          best = b.name; 
          bestLen = b.norm.length; 
      } 
  } 
  return best;
}

function detectMonth(normQuery){
  const q = normQuery.replace(/[.,;:!?]/g,' ');
  for (const [word,label] of Object.entries(MONTH_WORDS)){ 
      if (q.includes(word)) return label; 
  } 
  return null;
}

function detectYear(normQuery, talentName){
  // Check explicit year
  const m = normQuery.match(/\b(20\d{2})\b/); 
  if (m) return m[1];
  
  // If talent matches, try to find max year for that talent
  if (talentName) {
      const rows = DATA.filter(r => norm(r[COLS.talent]) === norm(talentName));
      const years = rows.map(r => parseInt(String(r[COLS.year] ?? ''),10)).filter(Number.isFinite);
      return years.length ? String(Math.max(...years)) : "";
  }
  return "";
}

const QUERY_STOPWORDS = new Set(["di","de","del","della","dello","dei","degli","delle","da","dal","dalla","dallo","dai","dagli","dalle","la","il","lo","le","i","gli","e","a","in","su","per","con","tra","fra","mostra","vedi","dammi","trova","cerca","voglio","sapere","visualizza","elenca","analizza","apri","seleziona","tutti","tutte","tutto","tutta","anno","mese","mesi","brand","attivit√†","attivita","talent","creator","influencer","video","foto","post","reel","tiktok","stories","story","igs"]);

function hasRosterIntent(normQuery){
  return /\broster\b|\bscheda\b/.test(normQuery);
}

function openRosterFromQuery(talentName, isAll = false){
  searchMode = 'roster';
  sel = { talent: isAll ? '__ALL_TALENTS__' : talentName, year:"", month:"", brand:"", campaign:"" };
  step = 0;
  editing = false;
  talentSearch = "";
  bucketFilters = {};
  updateModeToggleIcon();
  renderAll();
  document.querySelector('.shell')?.scrollTo({top:0, behavior:'smooth'});
}

function applySelectionFromNatural(talentName, normQuery){
  // 1. Set Talent
  sel.talent = talentName;
  
  // 2. Set Year (detect or auto-max)
  sel.year = detectYear(normQuery, talentName) || "";
  
  // 3. Set Month
  sel.month = detectMonth(normQuery) || "__ALL_MONTHS__";
  
  // 4. Detect Brand
  // Clean query by removing already used tokens (Talent Name, Year, Month Words)
  let tokens = normQuery.replace(/[.,;:!?]/g,' ').split(/\s+/).filter(Boolean);
  
  // Remove Talent tokens
  if (talentName) {
      const talentTokens = norm(talentName).split(/\s+/);
      tokens = tokens.filter(t => !talentTokens.includes(t));
  }
  
  // Remove Year token
  if (sel.year) tokens = tokens.filter(t => t !== String(sel.year));
  
  // Remove Month tokens
  if (sel.month && sel.month !== "__ALL_MONTHS__") {
      for(const [mWord, mLabel] of Object.entries(MONTH_WORDS)) {
          if(mLabel === sel.month) { tokens = tokens.filter(t => t !== mWord); }
      }
  }
  
  const queryForBrand = tokens.join(' ');
  const detectedBrand = detectBrand(queryForBrand);
  
  let unknownBrandError = null;
  if (!detectedBrand) {
      // Check for residual words that are not stopwords
      const residual = tokens.filter(t => !QUERY_STOPWORDS.has(t)).join(' ');
      if (residual.length > 0) unknownBrandError = residual;
  }

  sel.brand  = detectedBrand || (unknownBrandError ? toTitleCase(unknownBrandError) : "__ALL__");
  sel.campaign = "";
  
  // Force Search Mode to Talent because we found a talent
  searchMode = 'talent';
  const modeMenuToggleBtn2 = document.getElementById('modeMenuToggle');
  if (modeMenuToggleBtn2) modeMenuToggleBtn2.classList.remove('active'); // ensure visual state matches

  const needsCampaign = sel.brand && sel.brand !== "__ALL__" && talentBrandHasCampaigns(sel.brand);
  step = needsCampaign ? 4 : 3;
  editing = !!needsCampaign;
  renderAll();
  
  // Scroll up
  document.querySelector('.shell')?.scrollTo({top:0, behavior:'smooth'});
  
  // Feedback
  const rows = rowsFiltered();
  if (rows.length === 0) {
      if (unknownBrandError) {
          const niceResidual = toTitleCase(unknownBrandError);
          setStateMessage(`L'attivit√† "${niceResidual}" non √® presente per ${sel.talent}.`, 'error');
      } else if (sel.brand && sel.brand !== "__ALL__") {
           setStateMessage(`Nessuna attivit√† trovata per ${sel.talent} con ${selectedBrandFullLabel()}${sel.year ? ` nel ${sel.year}`:''}.`, 'error');
      } else {
          setStateMessage(`Nessun dato disponibile per questa selezione.`, 'error');
      }
  } else { 
      setStateMessage(''); 
  }
  
  els.nlInput.value = "";
}

function handleNaturalQuerySubmit(){
  const raw = (els.nlInput.value || "").trim();
  els.state.textContent = ""; 
  pendingQuery = null; 
  els.nlAmbiguity.style.display = "none"; 
  els.nlAmbiguity.innerHTML = "";
  
  if (!raw){ setStateMessage("Scrivi una richiesta nella barra in basso.", 'error'); return; }
  if (els.modeMenuModal && els.modeMenuModal.classList.contains('open')) {
    closeModeMenu();
  }
  
  const nq = norm(raw);
  const rosterIntent = hasRosterIntent(nq);
  if (rosterIntent){
    const rosterCandidates = detectRosterTalentCandidates(nq);
    const wantsAll = /\btutti\b|\btutte\b|\btutto\b|\ball\b/.test(nq);
    if (rosterCandidates.length > 1){
      pendingQuery = { normQuery: nq, candidates: [...rosterCandidates], mode: 'roster' };
      setStateMessage("Ho trovato pi√π talent nel roster, scegli quale vedere.");
      els.nlAmbiguity.style.display = "flex";
      els.nlAmbiguity.innerHTML = `<span class="muted">Quale talent intendevi?</span>` + rosterCandidates.map(name => `<button class="chip btn" data-talent-choice="${escAttr(name)}">${esc(name)}</button>`).join('');
      return;
    }
    if (rosterCandidates.length === 1){
      openRosterFromQuery(rosterCandidates[0]);
      els.nlInput.value = "";
      return;
    }
    if (wantsAll){
      openRosterFromQuery('', true);
      els.nlInput.value = "";
      return;
    }
    setStateMessage("Non ho capito quale talent vuoi vedere nel roster.", 'error');
    return;
  }
  const candidates = detectTalentCandidates(nq);
  
  // CASE A: Talent found
  if (candidates.length > 0){
      if (candidates.length > 1){
        // Ambiguity
        pendingQuery = { normQuery: nq, candidates: [...candidates] };
        setStateMessage("Ho trovato pi√π talent, scegli quale vedere.");
        els.nlAmbiguity.style.display = "flex";
        els.nlAmbiguity.innerHTML = `<span class="muted">Quale talent intendevi?</span>` + candidates.map(name => `<button class="chip btn" data-talent-choice="${escAttr(name)}">${esc(name)}</button>`).join('');
        return;
      }
      // Single match
      applySelectionFromNatural(candidates[0], nq);
      return;
  }
  
  // CASE B: No Talent found -> Check for BRAND only
  const brandOnly = detectBrand(nq);
  if (brandOnly) {
      // Switch mode to BRAND
      searchMode = 'brand';
      const modeMenuToggleBtn3 = document.getElementById('modeMenuToggle');
      if (modeMenuToggleBtn3) modeMenuToggleBtn3.classList.add('active'); // Visual update
      
      sel.brand = brandOnly;
      sel.campaign = "";
      sel.talent = ""; 
      sel.year = ""; 
      sel.month = ""; 
      
      step = 1; // Go to next step in Brand mode
      editing = true;
      renderAll();
      document.querySelector('.shell')?.scrollTo({top:0, behavior:'smooth'});
      
      const needsCampaign = brandModeHasCampaigns(sel.brand);
      const nextLabel = needsCampaign ? "Ora scegli la Campagna." : "Ora scegli il Talent.";
      setStateMessage(`Ho selezionato l'attivit√† "${brandOnly}". ${nextLabel}`);
      els.nlInput.value = "";
      return;
  }

  // CASE C: Nothing found
  setStateMessage("Non ho capito. Prova a scrivere 'Nome Talent' oppure 'Nome Brand'.", 'error'); 
}

/* Event Listener for Ambiguity Chips */
els.nlAmbiguity.addEventListener('click', (e)=>{
  const btn = e.target.closest('[data-talent-choice]');
  if (!btn || !pendingQuery) return;
  const choice = btn.getAttribute('data-talent-choice');
  if (pendingQuery.mode === 'roster') {
    openRosterFromQuery(choice);
  } else {
    applySelectionFromNatural(choice, pendingQuery.normQuery);
  }
  pendingQuery = null; 
  els.nlAmbiguity.style.display = "none"; 
  els.nlAmbiguity.innerHTML = "";
});

els.nlSubmit.onclick = handleNaturalQuerySubmit;
els.nlInput.addEventListener("keydown", (e) => {
  if (e.key === "Enter") {
    e.preventDefault();
    handleNaturalQuerySubmit();
  }
});
 


/* Helper to load Followers sheet with fallbacks */
async function loadFollowersData(baseJson){
  const isFollowersRows = (arr)=> Array.isArray(arr) && arr.length > 0 && arr.some(r=> r && (
      'NOME TALENT' in r || 'TALENT' in r || 'NOME' in r ||
      'PIATTAFORMA' in r || 'PLATFORM' in r || 'FOLLOWER' in r || 'FOLLOWERS' in r || 'SUBSCRIBERS' in r
  ));

  console.log('[FOLLOWERS] Tento caricamento da baseJson...');
  try {
    // Try to find in same JSON payload - prova varie chiavi
    const keys = ['FOLLOWER', 'Follower', 'follower', 'FOLLOWERS', 'Followers', 'followers', 'Roster', 'roster'];
    for (const k of keys){
      const guess = baseJson && baseJson[k];
      if (isFollowersRows(guess)) {
        console.log(`[FOLLOWERS] ‚úì Trovato in json.${k} con ${guess.length} righe`);
        return guess;
      }
    }
  } catch(e){ console.warn('[FOLLOWERS] Errore lettura baseJson:', e); }

  // Se non trovato nel JSON principale, prova a fetchare separatamente
  console.log('[FOLLOWERS] Non trovato in baseJson, tento fetch separato...');
  const paramCandidates = ['sheet','tab','range','ws','worksheet','name','foglio'];
  const valueCandidates = ['FOLLOWER', 'Follower', 'follower', 'FOLLOWERS', 'Followers'];
  for (const p of paramCandidates){
    for (const v of valueCandidates){
      try {
        const url = API_URL.includes('?') ? `${API_URL}&${p}=${encodeURIComponent(v)}` : `${API_URL}?${p}=${encodeURIComponent(v)}`;
        const res = await fetch(url);
        if (!res.ok) continue;
        const js = await res.json();
        const arr = Array.isArray(js) ? js : (Array.isArray(js.data) ? js.data : js[v] || js.FOLLOWER || js.followers || js.FOLLOWERS);
        if (isFollowersRows(arr)) {
          console.log(`[FOLLOWERS] ‚úì Trovato con ?${p}=${v}, ${arr.length} righe`);
          return arr;
        }
      } catch(e){ /* try next */ }
    }
  }
  console.warn('[FOLLOWERS] ‚ö†Ô∏è Nessun dato follower caricato');
  return [];
}

/* INIT ‚Äì versione con log + sempre nascondi loader */
(async function init(){
  // INIT LOGO AGENZIA
  const logoEl = document.getElementById('agencyLogo');
  if (logoEl && AGENCY_LOGO_URL) logoEl.src = AGENCY_LOGO_URL;

  console.log("Init avviato, chiamo API:", API_URL);

  try {
    const res = await fetch(API_URL);
    console.log("Fetch completato, status:", res.status);

    if (!res.ok) {
      throw new Error("HTTP " + res.status + " durante la chiamata all'API");
    }

    const json = await res.json();
    console.log("Risposta API parsata:", json);

    // Normalizza il formato della risposta
    let rawData = [];
    if (Array.isArray(json)) {
      rawData = json;
    } else if (Array.isArray(json.data)) {
      rawData = json.data;
    } else {
      throw new Error("Formato risposta inatteso dalla API (non √® un array n√© json.data √® un array)");
    }
    
    // Normalizzazione Dati (Clean Data)
    DATA = rawData.map(r => {
      // Fix Condivisioni typo
      const newRow = (r['CONDIVISIONI']==null && r['CONDIVIONE']!=null) ? ({...r, CONDIVISIONI: r['CONDIVIONE']}) : {...r};
      
      // Title Case Names/Brands
      if (newRow[COLS.talent]) newRow[COLS.talent] = toTitleCase(newRow[COLS.talent]);
      if (newRow[COLS.brand]) newRow[COLS.brand] = toTitleCase(newRow[COLS.brand]);
      
      // Fix IGS naming
      if (newRow[COLS.type]) {
          let t = toTitleCase(newRow[COLS.type]);
          t = t.replace(/\bigs\b/yi, "IGS");
          newRow[COLS.type] = t;
      }

      // ADV CHECK: Colonna "ADV" (o Q se l'header √® diverso, ma presumiamo ADV come da prompt)
      // Se il valore √® 'ADV' (case insensitive), setta true
      const advVal = String(r['ADV'] || '').trim().toUpperCase();
      newRow.isAdv = (advVal === 'ADV');

      return newRow;
    });

    console.log("Numero righe DATA:", DATA.length);

    // Followers load
    FOLLOWERS = await loadFollowersData(json);
    console.log("Numero righe FOLLOWERS:", FOLLOWERS.length);
    buildRosterVocab();

    buildVocabs();
    renderAll();
    preloadRosterImages();

  } catch(e){
    console.error("ERRORE INIT:", e);
    setStateMessage("Errore nel caricamento dei dati: " + e.message, "error");
  } finally {
    // In ogni caso tolgo il loader e mostro il frame
    loaderEl.style.opacity = '0';
    setTimeout(()=>{
      loaderEl.style.display = 'none';
      appFrameEl.style.display = 'flex';
      appFrameEl.classList.add('initial-menu');
      initialMenuOpen = true;
      openModeMenu();
    }, 300);
  }
})();
</script>
